revision.text:
'''Shijōnawate Shrine''' (四條畷神社, ''Shijōnawate jinja'') is a [[Shinto]] shrine located in [[Shijōnawate]] [[Osaka Prefecture]], Japan. Its main festival is held annually on February 12. It was founded in 1890, and enshrines [[Kusunoki Masatsura]] along with 24 other [[kami]]. It is one of the [[Fifteen Shrines of the Kenmu Restoration]].

==See also==
*[[Fifteen Shrines of the Kenmu Restoration]]

{{commonscat|Ikukunitama-jinja}}

==External links==
*[http://ikutamajinja.jp Official website]
*[http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/06/24/national/osakas-ikukunitama-shrine-set-revive-ritual-first-time-70-years/ Osaka's Ikukunitama Shrine set to revive ritual for first time in 70 years] 

{{DEFAULTSORT:Shijōnawate Shrine}}
{{Shinto shrine}}
{{Shinto-stub}}
[[Category:Shinto shrines in Osaka Prefecture]]
[[Category:Shinto shrines]]
[[Category:1890 establishments]]

{{unreferenced|date=August 2014}}

